title: Golf-Americans Woodland, Reavie in playoff at Phoenix Open
text:
February 4, 2018 / 11:00 PM / Updated 2 hours ago Golf-Americans Woodland, Reavie in playoff at Phoenix Open Reuters Staff 1 Min Read 
Feb 4 (Reuters) - Journeymen Gary Woodland and Chez Reavie will contest a playoff at the Phoenix Open after finishing the final round tied on Sunday. 
Woodland fired a closing seven-under-par 64, punctuated by a hat-trick of birdies from the 15th hole, to set a target of 18-under 266 at TPC Scottsdale in Arizona. 
Fellow American Reavie matched the total by sinking a 20-foot birdie at the last to shoot 66. Reporting by Andrew Both in Adelaide, South Australia, editing by Ed Osmond
